              White Box Testing Table


| **Aspect**            | **Description**                                                                                |
| --------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Definition**        | Testing the internal structure, logic, and code of an application.                             |
| **Tester View**       | Tester knows the internal code and logic (“white box”).                                        |
| **Focus Areas**       | Condition statements, loops, branches, paths, code flow.                                       |
| **Common Techniques** | • Statement Coverage  • Branch Coverage  • Path Coverage  • Loop Testing  • Condition Coverage |
| **Used By**           | Developers, White-box testers                                                                  |
| **Advantages**        | • Optimized code  • Early defect detection  • Ensures all logical paths are tested             |
| **Disadvantages**     | • Requires coding knowledge  • Time-consuming  • Complex for large systems                     |
| **Best For**          | Unit testing, component testing                                                                |

